1
00:00:21,647 --> 00:00:25,048
<i>[Wesley]</i>
<i>She's either counting oxygen molecules...</i>

2
00:00:25,151 --> 00:00:28,279
or analyzing the petri dish
she just put into her mouth.

3
00:00:28,387 --> 00:00:30,787
<i>Or sleeping.</i>
<i>I can never quite tell.</i>

4
00:00:30,890 --> 00:00:34,758
- You sure this is a good idea?
- We have plenty of petri dishes.

5
00:00:34,861 --> 00:00:36,385
- I meant...
- I know what you meant.

6
00:00:36,495 --> 00:00:40,556
- You don't have to do this all yourself.
- Who else is there?

7
00:00:40,666 --> 00:00:42,896
We're running out of people.
We're getting no further with Gunn...

8
00:00:43,002 --> 00:00:46,165
I'm not leaving Gunn in a hell dimension.
We'll get him out.

9
00:00:48,341 --> 00:00:51,538
<i>In the meantime, I need you</i>
<i>to let us help you with her.</i>

10
00:00:51,644 --> 00:00:53,839
<i>- She's my responsibility.</i>
- She's our responsibility.

11
00:00:53,946 --> 00:00:56,574
If she's gonna be here, there are things
that we should be doing.

12
00:00:56,682 --> 00:01:00,083
Testing her powers, studying her.

13
00:01:01,721 --> 00:01:03,951
She put a whole petri dish
in her mouth?

14
00:01:04,056 --> 00:01:06,650
<i>[Wesley]</i>
<i>Illyria can be...</i>

15
00:01:06,759 --> 00:01:09,626
<i>diffiicult.</i>

16
00:01:09,729 --> 00:01:13,130
Testing her might be hard without
getting someone seriously hurt.

17
00:01:14,267 --> 00:01:16,997
- We'll make Spike do it.
- Good.

18
00:01:21,741 --> 00:01:24,073
She doesn't understand
our world.

19
00:01:26,679 --> 00:01:29,614
She needs someone to guide her.
She needs...

20
00:01:29,715 --> 00:01:31,444
When was the last time
you slept?

21
00:01:33,753 --> 00:01:35,812
You're not her savior.

22
00:01:35,922 --> 00:01:41,189
I need you here, working, not off drinking
yourself into a coma, chasing ghosts.

23
00:01:42,995 --> 00:01:46,021
Fred's dead, Wes.
You're still alive.

24
00:01:47,667 --> 00:01:49,635
Start acting like it.

25
00:01:58,978 --> 00:02:01,947
We didn't know where else to go.

26
00:02:02,048 --> 00:02:04,812
Our son was
getting the mail.

27
00:02:04,917 --> 00:02:06,908
We could see him
from the living room.

28
00:02:07,019 --> 00:02:10,420
He was walking across the driveway,
and this van...

29
00:02:10,523 --> 00:02:13,924
It must've been goin' 50,
60 miles an hour.

30
00:02:14,026 --> 00:02:17,291
It hopped the curb,
and it ran right into him.

31
00:02:17,396 --> 00:02:19,296
<i>It slammed him right into</i>
<i>the side of the garage...</i>

32
00:02:19,398 --> 00:02:22,890
<i>and then...</i>
<i>backed up and sped off.</i>

33
00:02:24,070 --> 00:02:26,937
And the police think
this was intentional.

34
00:02:27,039 --> 00:02:29,599
- Has Homicide found the van?
- You don't understand.

35
00:02:29,709 --> 00:02:31,336
Our son's not dead.

36
00:02:32,778 --> 00:02:34,712
- He's not?
<i>- [Man] No.</i>

37
00:02:34,814 --> 00:02:39,183
- He's fine. The van hit him, and he got right up.
- He hardly has a scratch on him.

38
00:02:39,285 --> 00:02:42,277
<i>Police said it was dumb luck.</i>
<i>But if you saw it...</i>

39
00:02:42,388 --> 00:02:46,347
One of the officers called us later,
said our son might be different.

40
00:02:46,459 --> 00:02:51,590
<i>He mentioned that there was a law firm in</i>
<i>Los Angeles that dealt with... things like this.</i>

41
00:02:51,697 --> 00:02:54,359
Harmony, would you ask Angel
to come in here, please?

42
00:02:57,236 --> 00:02:59,932
Our son's downstairs. He thinks
that we're here to set up a trust.

43
00:03:00,039 --> 00:03:02,599
We didn't know
what else to tell him.

44
00:03:02,708 --> 00:03:07,941
- Please, will you help us?
- Of course.

45
00:03:11,517 --> 00:03:13,485
<i>[Connor]</i>
<i>Hey, Dad.</i>

46
00:04:18,451 --> 00:04:20,351
What...

47
00:04:20,453 --> 00:04:23,013
- What are you...
- Dad?

48
00:04:23,122 --> 00:04:24,817
<i>Yeah, it's okay.</i>
<i>Come on over.</i>

49
00:04:28,828 --> 00:04:31,558
You know, they have dried scorpions
in the vending machines downstairs.

50
00:04:31,664 --> 00:04:34,599
Angel, good. This is Laurence
and Colleen Reilly...

51
00:04:34,700 --> 00:04:36,634
- and this is their son...
- Connor. Hi.

52
00:04:36,735 --> 00:04:39,203
- Nice to meet you.
<i>- The Reillys need to talk about some issues...</i>

53
00:04:39,305 --> 00:04:41,796
