<i>and I thought we could...</i>
- No.

54
00:04:41,907 --> 00:04:43,898
- What?
- I'm sorry.

55
00:04:44,009 --> 00:04:48,207
There must be some mistake.
We can't help you.

56
00:04:52,017 --> 00:04:57,080
A van ran him down.
He got up and walked away... unharmed.

57
00:04:57,189 --> 00:05:00,420
- How did they find us?
<i>- Apolice offiicer mentioned our name.</i>

58
00:05:00,526 --> 00:05:03,017
Said we might
be able to help.

59
00:05:06,365 --> 00:05:08,799
- We're not taking this case.
- Why not?

60
00:05:08,901 --> 00:05:10,892
Because with everything
goin' on, we don't have time...

61
00:05:11,003 --> 00:05:12,971
to be dealing with
small stuff like this.

62
00:05:13,072 --> 00:05:16,906
"Small stuff'? This is what we do.
Or what we're supposed to do.

63
00:05:17,009 --> 00:05:20,001
They need help.
They seem like good people.

64
00:05:20,112 --> 00:05:22,205
All the more reason
to get 'em out of here.

65
00:05:22,314 --> 00:05:24,373
We know what this place
does to good people.

66
00:05:52,311 --> 00:05:53,744
[Screams]

67
00:06:00,352 --> 00:06:03,082
What was it?

68
00:06:03,189 --> 00:06:06,989
What am l...
I was lookin' for somethin'.

69
00:06:12,665 --> 00:06:14,929
[Loudly]
It's okay.

70
00:06:15,034 --> 00:06:17,002
Found it.

71
00:06:21,774 --> 00:06:24,470
<i>- [Punch Lands]</i>
- [Groans]

72
00:06:24,577 --> 00:06:27,171
You break so easily.

73
00:06:28,614 --> 00:06:31,242
Why do you bother
getting back up?

74
00:06:32,384 --> 00:06:35,717
Right. We need to set
some ground rules.

75
00:06:35,821 --> 00:06:38,016
First off, no more
punching me in the face.

76
00:06:38,123 --> 00:06:40,921
Secondly, when I
punch you in the face...

77
00:06:41,026 --> 00:06:42,823
you tell me how you feel...

78
00:06:42,928 --> 00:06:45,192
so I can write that down
on my clipboard.

79
00:06:46,699 --> 00:06:49,361
Third, no touchin'
my clipboard. Fourth...

80
00:06:49,468 --> 00:06:52,869
- I enjoy hurting you.
- We're gonna have to fix that, 'cause I'm...

81
00:07:01,981 --> 00:07:03,346
<i>[Spike Groaning]</i>

82
00:07:05,551 --> 00:07:08,520
- How goes it?
<i>- I've been hitting the half-breed.</i>

83
00:07:08,621 --> 00:07:10,350
He makes noise.

84
00:07:11,757 --> 00:07:13,884
We're off to a bit
of a rough start.

85
00:07:13,993 --> 00:07:16,188
But don't worry.
I'll break her.

86
00:07:16,295 --> 00:07:18,729
She's not a horse, Spike.

87
00:07:18,831 --> 00:07:22,858
<i>You know, this room is equipped</i>
<i>with automated training devices.</i>

88
00:07:22,968 --> 00:07:26,734
<i>You don't have to test her</i>
<i>byjust allowing her to pummel you.</i>

89
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:30,172
We're workin' on the basics.
But don't worry. I'm writing it all down.

90
00:07:30,276 --> 00:07:32,642
Okay, fine.

91
00:07:32,745 --> 00:07:36,704
You reek of frustration.
Curls off of you like smoke.

92
00:07:36,815 --> 00:07:38,942
Actually, luv, we call that scotch.

93
00:07:39,051 --> 00:07:41,019
Twelve-year Lagavulin,
if I'm not mistaken.

94
00:07:41,120 --> 00:07:43,213
<i>Good choice.</i>

95
00:07:43,322 --> 00:07:45,222
It's nothing.
I'm just, uh...

96
00:07:45,324 --> 00:07:48,487
I had a slight disagreement
with Angel.

97
00:07:48,594 --> 00:07:51,256
<i>Oh, old broody pants</i>
<i>got you wound up, eh?</i>

98
00:07:51,363 --> 00:07:54,696
<i>Keep in mind he can't get laid</i>
<i>without maybe goin'crazy.</i>

99
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,700
- It makes it funny.
- In my time...

100
00:07:56,802 --> 00:07:58,702
a leader would punish
your insolence with death.

101
00:07:58,804 --> 00:08:01,773
- We're not being insolent, Illyria.
- I am.

102
00:08:01,874 --> 00:08:07,403
It's just, uh, I don't
always understand Angel.

103
00:08:07,513 --> 00:08:09,413
Yet you
follow him willingly.

104
00:08:09,515 --> 00:08:14,214
- You're loyal to him.
- He's earned it.

105
00:08:14,320 --> 00:08:19,189
<i>- I trust he knows what he's doing.</i>
<i>- [Door Opens]</i>

106
00:08:19,291 --> 00:08:24,024
- What the hell is goin' on?
- Angel? I'm at your disposal.

107
00:08:24,129 --> 00:08:25,721
My son walks in
through my door!

108
00:08:25,831 --> 00:08:28,061
And you make him walk right out again.
I found that interesting.

109
00:08:28,167 --> 00:08:30,431
I want him as far away
from here as possible.

110
00:08:30,536 --> 00:08:34,131
Yes. It might have been smart to
get some information out of him first.

111
00:08:34,239 --> 00:08:36,639
- It could help us understand what's happening.
<i>- I'll tell you what.</i>

112
00:08:36,742 --> 00:08:38,710
Why don't you just tell me?

113
00:08:38,811 --> 00:08:40,836
Let's be clear about this.

114
00:08:40,946 --> 00:08:42,914
Things run differently now.

115
00:08:43,015 --> 00:08:45,210
I'm not a little girl,
and you and I...

116
00:08:45,317 --> 00:08:47,285
won't be making love
on this couch anytime soon.

117
00:08:48,687 --> 00:08:51,315
And with that in mind,
how can I help you?

118
00:08:56,995 --> 00:08:59,429
The senior partners
and I had a deal.

119
00:08:59,531 --> 00:09:01,726
<i>Yes, you did.</i>
<i>They took your son...</i>

120
00:09:01,834 --> 00:09:04,268
your raging,
psychopathic son...

121
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:06,565
gave him a new family,
changed his memories...

122
00:09:06,672 --> 00:09:08,799
changed everyone's memories,
actually...

123
00:09:08,907 --> 00:09:11,740
<i>in order to give him a new life,</i>
<i>a normal life.</i>

124
00:09:11,844 --> 00:09:14,312
- And I came to work here.
<i>- And we couldn't be happier.</i>

125
00:09:14,413 --> 00:09:16,847
The senior partners
honor their deals.

126
00:09:16,949 --> 00:09:19,509
<i>And believe me,</i>
<i>they have no desire to upset...</i>

127
00:09:19,618 --> 00:09:23,145
<i>such a profitable partnership.</i>

128
00:09:24,423 --> 00:09:29,554
So this is just a...
an unfortunate coincidence.

129
00:09:29,661 --> 00:09:32,095
<i>Oh, no, I didn't say that.</i>
<i>I said the senior partners...</i>

130
00:09:32,197 --> 00:09:34,097
weren't behind it.

131
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:36,531
This isn't an accident.

132
00:09:36,635 --> 00:09:39,798
Someone out there's
trying to send you a message...

133
00:09:39,905 --> 00:09:41,805
and they're using
your son to do it.

134
00:09:48,781 --> 00:09:50,976
Where are we
supposed to go now?

135
00:09:52,818 --> 00:09:57,312
I'm sure there's someone else
who can, uh, handle our trust.

136
00:09:59,725 --> 00:10:04,719
Um, just so you know, you guys
don't have to keep pretending.

137
00:10:04,830 --> 00:10:08,231
- I know we were there because of the van thing.
- Oh.

138
00:10:08,333 --> 00:10:11,302
- I'm sorry, honey. It's just... It was...
- It's cool.

139
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:15,965
My parents are liars, and I can never
trust them again, but it's cool.

140
00:10:16,074 --> 00:10:18,406
Look, I know
you guys are worried...

141
00:10:18,510 --> 00:10:22,276
but the whole point
is I'm okay.

142
00:10:22,381 --> 00:10:24,212
I got hit, and I'm okay.
That should make you happy...

143
00:10:24,316 --> 00:10:27,308
not like, you know,
mental patients.

144
00:10:27,419 --> 00:10:31,185
I mean, it turned out fine.

145
00:10:31,290 --> 00:10:33,485
[Mr. Reilly]
It's the getting-hit part.

146
00:10:33,592 --> 00:10:35,492
We thought you were dead.

147
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:38,791
- [Connor] Hey, have some faith in me.
- Connor...

148
00:10:38,897 --> 00:10:42,560
<i>[Connor]</i>
<i>All right. Look, you guys.</i>

149
00:10:42,668 --> 00:10:45,603
I'm not saying
this isn't weird and all.

150
00:10:45,704 --> 00:10:48,935
But we'll get through it.
You don't have to be scared.

151
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:54,703
- [Mrs. Reilly Screaming]
- [Mr. Reilly Shouting]

152
00:10:58,951 --> 00:11:00,885
<i>[Mr. Reilly]</i>
<i>Get off...</i>

153
00:11:00,986 --> 00:11:02,886
- Hey!
- [Screaming Continues]

154
00:11:02,988 --> 00:11:05,513
Mom!

155
00:11:08,894 --> 00:11:10,919
<i>[Mrs. Reilly Sobbing]</i>

156
00:11:11,029 --> 00:11:12,621
Whoa.

157
00:11:12,731 --> 00:11:15,461
[Growling]

158
00:11:43,996 --> 00:11:47,727
- Oh, my God!
- Connor, listen to me.

159
00:11:47,833 --> 00:11:49,824
You almost broke
that guy in half.

160
00:11:51,003 --> 00:11:52,994
That was awesome!

161
00:11:58,343 --> 00:12:00,834
Seriously, that was the coolest
thing I've ever seen.

162
00:12:00,946 --> 00:12:03,312
Well, it's not a big deal.

163
00:12:03,415 --> 00:12:05,474
I mean, I do stuff like that a lot.

164
00:12:05,584 --> 00:12:08,610
- There was this one time in France...
<i>- [Mrs. Reilly] Connor.!</i>

165
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:12,417
Dad. Dad.

166
00:12:12,524 --> 00:12:15,357
- I'm okay.
- We need to get him to a hospital.

167
00:12:15,460 --> 00:12:17,428
<i>We got doctors at Wolfram and Hart.</i>
<i>We can help.</i>

168
00:12:17,529 --> 00:12:20,692
And you and I have some things
we should probably talk about.

169
00:12:22,134 --> 00:12:24,602
Yeah, I kind of figured.

170
00:12:27,072 --> 00:12:29,540
Your dad's gonna be fine.
He's in good hands.

171
00:12:29,641 --> 00:12:33,737
Or claws, as the case may be.
They're good doctors.

172
00:12:33,845 --> 00:12:35,779
What were those things
that attacked us?

173
00:12:35,881 --> 00:12:38,543
Some kind of demon.
We're lookin' into it.

174
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:41,084
Is that what I am?
Some kind of demon?

175
00:12:44,089 --> 00:12:47,286
- No.
- Then what am I?

176
00:12:47,392 --> 00:12:52,420
The best we can tell, you're a healthy,
well-adjusted kid...

177
00:12:52,531 --> 00:12:55,796
with, uh,
enhanced abilities.

178
00:12:55,901 --> 00:12:58,131
And you're a vampire.

179
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:04,606
So, demons, vampires,
doctors with claws...

180
00:13:04,710 --> 00:13:08,476
and I'm some sort
of superhero.

181
00:13:09,815 --> 00:13:11,783
Okay.

182
00:13:15,020 --> 00:13:16,920
You're taking this
pretty well.

183
00:13:17,022 --> 00:13:19,149
What am I supposed to do,
complain?

184
00:13:19,257 --> 00:13:21,418
I just don't know how
I'm gonna explain it to my parents.

185
00:13:21,526 --> 00:13:23,960
You got family?

186
00:13:24,062 --> 00:13:26,030
- No.
- Right. Vampire.

187
00:13:26,131 --> 00:13:28,725
So, what are you,
like, 500 years old?

188
00:13:28,834 --> 00:13:31,928
No, I'm, uh...
Do I look 500?

189
00:13:32,037 --> 00:13:34,597
Do you spend all your time
making out with other vampires...

190
00:13:34,706 --> 00:13:36,606
like in Anne Rice novels?

191
00:13:36,708 --> 00:13:40,872
No. Well, I used to, but...

192
00:13:40,979 --> 00:13:43,539
- You have a girlfriend at least?
- I can't afford to.

193
00:13:43,649 --> 00:13:46,117
- Must be lonely.
- I keep busy.

194
00:13:46,218 --> 00:13:49,813
<i>Right. So, you guys,</i>
<i>like, fight crime...</i>

195
00:13:49,921 --> 00:13:51,889
and save the world here,
that sort of stuff?

196
00:13:51,990 --> 00:13:54,584
- Well, that's the idea.
- Wow.

197
00:13:54,693 --> 00:13:57,389
Is everyone here a superhero?
This place must be insane.

198
00:13:57,496 --> 00:14:00,192
It's mostly paralegals and secretaries.
Pretty boring, really.

199
00:14:03,802 --> 00:14:06,396
You filthy harlot!

200
00:14:06,505 --> 00:14:08,803
I'm gonna tear your neck out!

201
00:14:12,411 --> 00:14:14,971
